<subSubSection id="C3176555FFC3FFA8FF59FBF6EED5ACDE" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB236DEFFC3FFA8FF59FBF6EED5ACDE" blockId="10.[151,1437,1122,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis id="B979EACCFFC3FFA8FF59FBF6EA57AC67" bold="true" box="[151,274,1122,1148]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Hypopygial anal point with spoon-shaped apex—round with margin smooth or flattened with margin toothed. Superior volsella more or less heart-shaped, with median margin concave slightly at least. Digitus welldeveloped, extending beyond median margin of superior volsella. Frontal tubercles long, length/width ratio ~2–4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
